1) cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper investigates the performance of sparse vector recovery algorithms from compressive measurements, which is a topic closely related to information theory. 
2) cs.SP (Signal Processing): The paper deals with the recovery of sparse signals, which is a common problem in signal processing. 
3) cs.LG (Machine Learning): Sparse vector recovery is also a topic of interest in machine learning, particularly in the context of feature selection and dimensionality reduction. 
4) cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses the performance of various recovery algorithms, which involves numerical analysis techniques. 
5) cs.MM (Multimedia): Sparse signal recovery is also relevant in multimedia applications, such as image and video compression.
